<p>Maybe you should consider an object-oriented structure instead of inner functions. For example:</p>

<pre><code>var calculate = {
    number: 0,
    init: function (num) {
        this.number = num;
    },
    add: function (val) {
        this.number += val;
    },
    rem: function (val) {
        this.number -= val;
    }
};
</code></pre>

<p>And read the result from the calculate.number variable, who needs "return" anyway.</p>
